Adding puppet-usm module

Unified Software Management (USM) needs a puppet module
to setup its authenticated endpoints, ports, etc..

The puppet-usm is not explicitly added to the ISO.
It gets pulled in through the puppet-manifests dependency.

Note: this follows the same algorithm and code paths that
are used for setting up patching through puppet.

The USM ports are:
 API port (private): 5493
 Controller port:    5494
 Agent port:         5495
 API port (auth):    5497
 Admin port (auth):  5498

Default URLS: (pre bootstrap these are not in keystone)
 Private URL http://127.0.0.1:5497/v1
 Public  URL http://127.0.0.1:15497/v1
 Admin   URL http://127.0.0.1:5497/v1

After bootstrap (DC mode) endpoints look like
 SystemController internal  http://192.168.204.2:25497/
 SystemController public    http://10.10.10.2:25497/
 SystemController admin     https://192.168.204.2:25498/

 RegionOne internal  http://192.168.204.2:5497
 RegionOne public    http://10.10.10.2:15497
 RegionOne admin     https://192.168.204.2:5498

Note: a sysinv change enables this puppet code and testing
was also done with that code.

Test Plan:
  PASS: Build/bootstrap/unlock AIO-SX
  PASS: Build/bootstrap/unlock STD (2 controllers)

commit.message:
(SIMP-689) Move dep management to librarian-puppet

Before this commit, dependency repos were tracked using git submodules.

The patch removes the git submodules, moves dependency repo management
to librarian-puppet, and introduces several new rake tasks:

`deps:checkout` will check out each dependency repo to the latest commit
                in the branch specified in `Puppetfile.tracking`.

`deps:checkout[stable]` will check out each dependency repo to the ref
                        specified for it in `Puppetfile.stable`.

`deps:record` will regenerate `Puppetfile.stable` according to the
              current local ref of each repository in
              `Puppetfile.tracking`.

Ensure lxml and its dependencies are installed before messytables.

Messytables has a pip dependency on lxml which is not represented in the management
dependencies in puppet package. This means the messytables install may break if it is
pipped in before the lxml libxml regular dependencies.

commit.message:
(maint) Remove Gemfile.lock

Without this patch the Gemfile.lock is committed to the repository,
which is a problem because the Gemfile has relaxed the specification of
dependency versions, particularly for beaker and the ability to install
from a Git HEAD.  This is a problem because the Gemfile.lock is no
longer a single source of truth and will be frequently in conflict.

puppet-server follows the lead of puppet with regard to branching,
merging and Gemfile dependency management.  Puppet deleted this file
from their repository back in 2012 in commit
c6b8e7fce004ea393f7821b6e576568cc77f035b, so this patch follows their
lead.

commit.message:
Allow to skip management of python dev package

Just like we can skip managing the pip and venv packages, allow to
opt-out of managing the dev package.

Enforcing a state of these packages sometimes cause trouble if the user
of the module does not care about them but they get installed as another
package dependency (e.g. syslog-ng-mod-python depends on python-venv, by
default python-venv is ensured absent, so on each run Puppet wants to
install syslog-ng-mod-python (which install python-venv as a dependency)
or remove python-venv (which remove syslog-ng-mod-python as a
dependency)).  This can be avoided using the corresponding
`manage_XXX_package` paramater, but `manage_dev_package` was missing.
